x4freetext: For each reaction, light particles, H
and He, were observed with two three-member Si
detectors were calibrated by normalizing a pulser to
the peak due to the 5.48 MeV alpha-particle decay of
241Am. A large position sensitive four anode
ionization chamber telescope was used to detect
evaporation residues and other heavy reaction products.
